Machine Specific Notes:
=======================
 
1. This release of C-ISAM is built on Linux Kernel 2.6.9-34.ELsmp on x86_64 
   and Glibc glibc-2.3.2-95.27 and certified on RHEL 5 2.6.18-8.el5xen 

   This product is built with gcc compiler version 3.4.5 on 
   Red Hat Linux 3.4.5-2.
 
2. This release supports C-ISAM files (index files, data files, transaction
   files and audit trail files) of size greater than 2GB using special
   APIs which are described in the operating system man pages
 
3. Refer to the information provided in the release notes in order
   to migrate to this version of C-ISAM.
 
4. Ensure that the "ulimit" value is set appropriately so that
   files of size greater than 2GB can be created by C-ISAM.

5. When building applications using the dynamic C-ISAM libraries provided
   with this release, the C compiler options "-fwritable-strings -fpic 
   -fomit-frame-pointer" need to be used.

